And if you do American crosswords with any regularity and *don't* know Alan ALDA, that's quite unreasonable of you. Both his given and surnames, along with the proper names OSLO, TERI and ONO (not to mention OARS, EMU and ADO) are the very essence of crosswordese. You'd do well to memorize them - or perhaps find a different pastime?

