@Grant

Aubergine is my wife's and mine favorite vegetable. We love it in any form, and baba ghanouj, which me more often call mutabbal, is our breakfast treat on slow Saturday mornings.

The dip is not slimy - it is made of blended, baked aubergine, so the texture some find unappealing is not an issue - but maybe I say so as a person who likes aubergine in general. With Middle Eastern spices (cumin mostly), lots of high quality olive oil, tahini, and garlic it's one of my favorite things to eat.

Andrzej,

If there is yogurt in it, it's mutabbal;
if not, it's baba ghanouj.

